{
  "manifest_version": 4,
  "readme": [
    "This manifest is the single source of truth for DevFlow's cloud capability policy:",
    "which tools/commands each execution tier (review, implement, command) may run.",
    "",
    "EDIT WORKFLOW: change a grant here (add/remove a token in a group or a profile's",
    "inline list), then regenerate with `python3 lib/generate-capability-profiles.py`.",
    "Never hand-edit the generated allowlist literals in the workflow files — the",
    "generated regions carry a banner with manifest_version + a per-region sha256 and",
    "`python3 lib/generate-capability-profiles.py --check` (run by lib/test/run.sh, so",
    "the required `lib + python tests` CI job gates it) turns any drift RED before merge.",
    "",
    "REVIEW SECURITY BOUNDARY: the `review` profile is the read-only reviewer allowlist",
    "run against a PR-head checkout. Widening it requires a deliberate visible diff to",
    "lib/review-profile.tokens (the lock) in the same PR — the generator never writes",
    "that lock, and any manifest edit (including to a shared group) that changes the",
    "resolved review list fails closed until the lock is updated to match.",
    "",
    "BUMP RULE: increment `manifest_version` exactly once in any PR that changes this",
    "file. Enforced by review convention (the generator reads no git history); the",
    "per-region checksums remain the machine-verified truth.",
    "",
    "Groups organize tokens for readability and are shared across profiles only where",
    "the contiguous token runs are genuinely identical; most runs are per-profile."
  ],
